<TITLE> ACC sues Harris Chowdhury, family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 8 (bdnews24.com)The Anticorruption Commission has filed a case against Harris Chowdhury, wife, children and six others, on charges of illegally acquiring wealth worth Tk 19.5 crore through misuse of power during the previous BNP-led government. According to the case details, Harris with the collusion of relatives acquired Tk 19.5 crore in assets while he was former prime minister Khaleda Zia's political secretary. ACC deputy director Jibon Krishna Roy filed the case with Gulshan Police Station, sub-inspector Syeda Zakia Sultana told bdnews24.com. All of the accused in the case, including Harris, have been fugitive since the current caretaker government took power. bdnews2
